daily_stats = sessions_history.copy().sort_values('session_date')

daily_users = (daily_stats
               .groupby('session_date')['user_id']
               .nunique()
               .reset_index(name='total_users'))

daily_reg_users = (daily_stats[daily_stats['registration_flag'] == 1]
                   .groupby('session_date')['user_id']
                   .nunique()
                   .reset_index(name='reg_users'))

result = pd.merge(daily_users, daily_reg_users, on='session_date', how='left').fillna(0)

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))
ax = plt.gca()  

plt.plot(result['session_date'], result['total_users'], 
         label='  ', marker='o', color='#6495ED')
plt.plot(result['session_date'], result['reg_users'], 
         label=' ', marker='s', color='#008B8B')

ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(mdates.DayLocator(interval=2))
ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%Y-%m-%d'))  
plt.xticks(rotation=45) 

plt.xlabel('', fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel(' ', fontsize=12)
plt.title('      ', pad=10, fontsize=14)
plt.legend(fontsize=12)
plt.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.5)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

from statsmodels.stats.power import NormalIndPower

alpha = 0.05  
beta = 0.2  
power = 1 - beta  
mde = 0.03  

power_analysis = NormalIndPower()

sample_size = power_analysis.solve_power(
    effect_size=mde,
    power=power,
    alpha=alpha,
    ratio=1      
)

print(f"     : {int(sample_size)}")

     : 17441

In [17]:
devices = ['Android', 'iPhone', 'PC', 'Mac']

contingency_table = pd.crosstab(
    sessions_test_part.drop_duplicates('user_id')['test_group'],
    sessions_test_part.drop_duplicates('user_id')['device']
)

# 0:             -  = b
# 1:              -  != b

results = []
for device in devices:
    count = np.array([
        contingency_table.loc['A', device],  
        contingency_table.loc['B', device]
    ])
    
    nobs = np.array([
        contingency_table.loc['A'].sum(),  
        contingency_table.loc['B'].sum()   
    ])
    
    z_stat, p_value = proportions_ztest(count, nobs, alternative='two-sided')
    
    results.append({
        '': device,
        'Z-': f"{z_stat:.3f}",
        'p-value': f"{p_value:.4f}",
        ' 0': '' if p_value < 0.05 else ''
    })

results_df = pd.DataFrame(results)
display(results_df)
Z- p-value 0
0 Android -0.628 0.5300
1 iPhone 1.165 0.2441
2 PC -0.626 0.5312
3 Mac 0.416 0.6776

regions = ['CIS', 'MENA', 'EU']

contingency_table = pd.crosstab(
    sessions_test_part.drop_duplicates('user_id')['test_group'],
    sessions_test_part.drop_duplicates('user_id')['region']
)

# 0:             -  = b
# 1:              -  != b

results = []
for region in regions:
    count = np.array([
        contingency_table.loc['A', region],  
        contingency_table.loc['B', region]
    ])
    
    nobs = np.array([
        contingency_table.loc['A'].sum(),  
        contingency_table.loc['B'].sum()   
    ])
    
    z_stat, p_value = proportions_ztest(count, nobs, alternative='two-sided')
    
    results.append({
        '': region,
        'Z-': f"{z_stat:.3f}",
        'p-value': f"{p_value:.4f}",
        ' 0': '' if p_value < 0.05 else ''
    })

results_df = pd.DataFrame(results)
display(results_df)

4.2. Проверка корректности результатов теста¶

, , .

  • , .

  • , .

:

  • $H_0: \mu_{\text{}} \leq \mu_{\text{}}$
    .
